column2: I have read the information, understood it, and agreed to participate.
column11: 1. In the last month, how often have you been upset because of something that happened unexpectedly?
column12: 2. In the last month, how often have you felt that you were unable to control the important things in your life?
column13: 3. In the last month, how often have you felt nervous and “stressed”?
column14: 4. In the last month, how often have you felt confident about your ability to handle your personal problems?
column15: 5. In the last month, how often have you felt that things were going your way?
column16: 6. In the last month, how often have you found that you could not cope with all the things that you had to do?
column17: 7. In the last month, how often have you been able to control irritations in your life?
column18: 8. In the last month, how often have you felt that you were on top of things?
column19: 9. In the last month, how often have you been angered because of things that were outside of your control?
column20: 10. In the last month, how often have you felt difficulties were piling up so high that you could not overcome them?
column21: How would you rate your overall academic workload?
column22: Does your university provide mental health resources to support stress management?
